name: Nana Yōkai Collection: Oni
description:
Nana Yōkai Collection is a series of illustrations, created with the aim of sharing traditional Japanese mythology. In this series, Nana will be personifying herself as different Yōkai (Japanese spirits).
Oni is one of the greatest icons of Japanese folklore. They are cruel and usually represent the punishers of Hell.
Oni is created when truly wicked humans die. Their appearance comes in many varieties but is most commonly depicted with red or blue skin, wild hair, two or more horns.
